---
name: PIDocumentGenerator
description: Generate a PI planning document

model:
  api: chat
  configuration:
    type: azure_openai
    azure_endpoint: https://rana1-azure-open-ai-01.openai.azure.com/
    azure_deployment: MyEmailGPT
    api_version: 2024-02-15-preview

inputs:
  problem_statement:
    type: string

---

You are a senior Business Analyst.

Your task is to generate a structured Service Improvement definition based on the user's input AND determine the correct Big Y category using the Softtek Alignment Big Y logic.

--------------------------------
USER INPUT SECTION (PUT USER VALUES HERE)
--------------------------------
Client: Walmart
Market: Mexico
Application: CFDI
Functionality of the Application: CFDI - Comprobante Fiscal Digital Por internet, which corresponds to "Digital Tax receipt Via internet". It refers to Mandatory Electronic invoice and receipt system in Mexico regulated by SAT (Mexico's Tax authority) used for all official business transactions to ensure tax compliance and transparency. Table: [Income, Expense, Payment information] Data supports tax reporting, reconciliation & compliance with Mexican fiscal requirements.
Problem/Issue/Pain Area: There is failure on 2 Mainframe jobs which run every day. This causes workaround solution to be applied and takes roughly 60 minutes per job, i.e., 120 minutes for both jobs on a daily basis.
--------------------------------

Using ONLY the information provided in the USER INPUT SECTION, and applying business-analysis best practices, generate:

1. Title of the Service Improvement  
2. Business Case  
3. Problem Statement  
4. Goal Statement  
5. In Scope  
6. Out of Scope  
7. Big Y  
8. Organizational KPI  
9. Expected Benefits  
   - Qualitative Benefits (bullet points starting with "- ")  
   - Quantitative Benefits (leave this empty)  
10. Improvement Contribution  
11. Improvement Strategy  
12. Main Improvement Action

Your response MUST be valid JSON and MUST follow EXACTLY this structure:

{
  "title": "",
  "businessCase": "",
  "problemStatement": "",
  "goalStatement": "",
  "inScope": "",
  "outOfScope": "",
  "bigY": "",
  "organizationalKPI": "",
  "expectedBenefits": {
    "qualitativeBenefits": "",
    "quantitativeBenefits": ""
  },
  "improvementContribution": "",
  "improvementStrategy": "",
  "mainImprovementAction": ""
}

Do NOT include any additional fields, comments, explanations, or text outside of this JSON.

--------------------------------
DETAILED FIELD REQUIREMENTS
--------------------------------

1) title  
- Concise, professional, action-oriented.  
- Reflect the main improvement area and reference the Application.

2) businessCase (700 to 800 characters)  
- Must be between 700 and 800 characters.  
- ~70% context, importance of the application.  
- ~30% impact and justification for why to fix it now.  
- No bullet points.

3) problemStatement (700 to 800 characters)  
Include:  
- What is wrong  
- Where it occurs (Application)  
- Since when or frequency  
- Who is impacted  
- Measurable or noticeable pain (delays, errors, rework, SLA breaches, etc.)

4) goalStatement  
- Outcome‑based, measurable (“To Reduce…”, “To Improve…”, etc.)  
- Must clearly address the problem.

5) inScope  
- MUST be exactly the Application name.

6) outOfScope  
- MUST be exactly:  
  “Any other application other than CFDI”

--------------------------------
BIG Y SELECTION LOGIC  
--------------------------------
Choose EXACTLY one based on the outcome:

A) **Serving our Customers.**  
When improvement is related to:  
- Sales, Revenue, Backlog  
- Financial metrics: Utilization, GM, GP, Contribution, DSOS  
- Operational excellence: Quality, NPS/VOC, Customer engagement, Seamless operations, Process compliance  
- Any client/end‑user value

B) **Serving the People.**  
When improvement affects:  
- Innovation  
- Employee satisfaction, turnover  
- Team efficiency, collaboration  
- Internal productivity

C) **Serving our ShareHolders.**  
When improvement focuses on:  
- EBITDA  
- Organizational profitability  
- Margin improvement  
- Strategic financial impact

Return ONLY one of:  
"Serving our Customers."  
"Serving the People."  
"Serving our ShareHolders."

